Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the deployment of femtocells in the vehicular environment to improve signal quality for mobile users. This falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture.
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper analyzes the capacity and outage probability of the proposed mobile femtocell deployment. This involves the use of information theory concepts and techniques.
3. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The improved signal quality provided by the femtocell deployment can enhance the multimedia experience of mobile users in the vehicular environment.
4. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper does not explicitly discuss security, but the deployment of femtocells in the vehicular environment may have security implications that fall under the domain of cryptography and security.
5. cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) - The paper does not involve significant computational aspects, but the deployment of femtocells in the vehicular environment may have engineering implications that fall under the domain of computational engineering.
